ABUJA, NIGERIA ~ THE country’s anti-corruption agency has arrested a man and his two sons for alleged spiritual fraud after they reportedly conned a woman of N4, 6 million (R212 000). The suspect allegedly demanded money to pray for the woman and connect her with his “spirits” so she could become rich. The suspect, his sons and an accomplice were bust while allegedly trying to extort an additional amount of N105 000 (R4 800) from the woman. Tony Orilade, acting spokesman of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, said: “Efforts are on to recover the money while the suspects will soon be arraigned in court.” – CAJ NEWS